--- Linked Issue #1913: [fix] v3.1.0 has broken the compatibility of compress ---
## Describe the bug

The v3.1.0 has broken the compatibility of compress.
The request will be blocked!

**Node.js version:** v25.0.0

**OS version:** win11 25h2

## Code to reproduce

```ts
import Koa from 'koa';
import fs from 'node:fs';
import compress from 'koa-compress';

const app = new Koa();

app.use(
  compress({
    br: false
  })
);

app.use(async ctx => {
  ctx.type = 'application/javascript';
  ctx.body = fs.createReadStream('index.js');
});

app.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log(`server run at: \x1b[36mhttp://127.0.0.1:3000\x1b[0m`);
});
```

## Checklist

- [x] I have searched through GitHub issues for similar issues.
- [x] I have completely read through the README and documentation.
- [x] I have tested my code with the latest version of Node.js and this package and confirmed it is still not working.

